[Black "7...Nf6 8.Qd1 with 10.a3! 0-0 11.Bf4"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 c5 4. cxd5 cxd4 5. Qa4+ Bd7 6. Qxd4 exd5 7. Qxd5 Nf6
8. Qd1 Nc6 9. Nf3 Bc5 10. a3
{ I was very surprised when I saw the computer giving this move as the best by far. There is a point behind it, as you will see later. I must confess that this is the only place in the whole Gambit where I found some real advantage for White ! }
10... O-O 11. Bf4
{ Another attempt to develop the bishop, and afterwards play e3. } 11... Qb6
12. e3
{ Honestly speaking, White is better here, but the moves are not easy to find. }
12... Bf5 13. Bb5 Ne4 14. Qe2 Nxc3 15. bxc3 Rad8 16. O-O a6 17. Bc4 Na5 18. Nd4
Nxc4 19. Qxc4 Be4
{ Once again White is better, but Black has some compensation. } *

