[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 c5 4. cxd5 cxd4 5. Qa4+ Bd7 6. Qxd4 exd5 7. Qxd5 Nf6
8. Qd1 Nc6 9. Nf3 Bc5 10. a3
{ I was very surprised when I saw the computer giving this move as the best by far. There is a point behind it, as you will see later. I must confess that this is the only place in the whole Gambit where I found some real advantage for White ! }
10... O-O 11. Bg5
{ The moves a3 and Bg5 seem a bit strange, one after another, but there is a point behind it. If Black plays ...Qb6, at some point, he doesn't really threaten ...Qxb2 because the queen, on b2, would be trapped ! }
11... h6 { Following Alekhine's ideas ! } 12. Bxf6 Qxf6
{ The computer doesn't realize how strong this is ! Now the situation becomes extremely interesting ! }
13. Qxd7 Rfd8 14. Qg4 Ne5 15. Qg3 Qb6
{ Black attacks the weaknesses on the queenside. } 16. Rb1
{ But now comes one of the best moves I've seen in my chess career. } 16...
Rac8
{ Black plays according to that principle of attacking chess: get all your pieces into the party. But to do this Black simply leaves his knight on e5 hanging, which is simply amazing ! }
17. Nxe5 Bxa3 18. Nd3 Rxc3 19. e4 Bb4 20. bxc3 Bxc3+ 21. Ke2 Qxb1 22. Qe3 a5
{ A piece down but the a-pawn is very fast... } *

