{ In this chapter we will have a look at the more difficult task to classify gambits. It makes sense to discuss them together. }
1. d4 d5
{ 1...Nf6  2.g4 ?!    The Gibbins-Weidenhagen Gambit. The situation is very similar to the previous line. If Black knows a few moves, the job is done !   1...e5 ?    The Charlick Gambit ! Also known as the Englund Gambit. It's not sound, but you'll still find people using it from time to time in blitz games. In what follows I present you with an easy refutation ! }
2. e4
{ The Blackmar-Diemer Gambit is very popular ! In just 2017 alone I could find more than 50 games playing this variation ! This means that there is some probability that you will face this gambit at some stage in your games ! }
2... dxe4 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. f3 { Here comes my fresh idea ! Keep on reading ! } *

