1. d4 e5
{ This is not the best gambit. Black gets some lead in development, but a central pawn is too much to sacrifice ! }
2. dxe5 Nc6 3. Nf3 Qe7
{ 3...d6  Black tries to develop as fast as possible, but White doesn't allow this.  4.Bg5 !   4.exd6 ?!  Bxd6  5.Nc3  Nf6  6.e3  O-O  This is the kind of game Black wants.  4...Qd7   4...f6  5.exf6  Nxf6  6.Nc3  ±  5.exd6  Bxd6  6.Nc3  Now the Bishop is developed on g5 and the Queen is misplaced on d7. White is much better.  h6  7.Bh4  Nge7  8.e4  ± }
4. Bg5
{ I like this the most, although other moves are good as well.   4.Nc3  Nxe5  5.e4  += }
4... Qb4+ { 4...Qe6  5.Nc3  Nxe5  6.e4 !  Bb4  7.Qd4  ± } 5. Nc3 Qxb2 6. Bd2
{ The key move. Now Black's Queen is almost trapped.   6.Nd5 ?!  Bb4+ !  7.Bd2  Bxd2+  8.Nxd2  Nb4 !?  is not so clear. }
6... Bb4 7. Rb1 Qa3 { 7...Qxc3  8.Bxc3  Bxc3+  9.Nd2  +- } 8. Nd5 Bxd2+ 9. Qxd2
*

