{ How should White play now? } 1. Nd5
{ Yes, sometimes I make good moves, as well ! } 1... Qxc4 2. Qh5
{ This was the key move ! I gave a pawn but suddenly all of my pieces are working together ! }
2... f5 { 16...Rac8 ?  17.f4  Ng6  18.Rf3 !  Followed by Rh3 and mate ! } 3. f4
{ 17.Nxc7  was simple, but I wanted more. } 3... Nd7 4. Rf3 Rf7 5. Rg3 Ne7 6.
Bxg7 Rxg7 7. Nxe7+ Kh8 8. Rxg7 Kxg7 9. Nxf5+ Kh8 10. Nd4
{ Here the position is completely winning. Anyway, have a look at the game till the end. I didn't lose a single bit of my advantage. }
10... Rg8 11. Qb5 Nb6 12. Qf5
{ The knight is worse on b6, because it cannot defend the kingside. } 12... Nd5
13. g3
{ After this move, the pressure on the g-file disappears. Now I will try to create threats on the kingside. }
13... Qc5 14. Kf2 c6 15. e4 Nb6 16. Qf6+
{ Many people would exchange queens to make things easier, but please, if you can, mate him ! }
16... Rg7 17. Kg2 Qh5 18. Re1 Qf7 19. Qd8+ Rg8 20. Qxb6
{ Now you can stop studying the game, if you want ! But if someone wants to check it till the end, be my guest. }
20... Qxf4 21. Nf5 Qd2+ 22. Qf2 Qd3 23. Qd4+ Qxd4 24. Nxd4 Re8 25. Kf3 Re5 26.
Nf5 Rb5 27. Re2 Rb3+ 28. Kf4 Rd3 29. e5 dxe5+ 30. Kxe5 h5 31. Kf6 Kh7 32. Re7+
