[SetUp "1"]

{ Black played 20... Qh4+. Was there something better ? } 1... Bf5
{ Once again, we should calculate the forced moves in this position. Do it all of the time ! }
2. e4 Rxc3
{ 21...Qh4+  22.Kg1  Bxg3  23.fxg3  Qxg3+  24.Kh1  This is good only for a draw. }
3. Bxc3 Qh4+ 4. Kg1 Bxg3 5. fxg3 Qxg3+ 6. Kh1 Qh4+ 7. Kg1 Bxe4
{ This is the difference ! Now White should give up the queen. } 8. Qxe4 Qxe4
{ Black will start slowly pushing the pawns on the kingside and probably manage to annoy White a little bit. Although the engine is very happy with Black, one should be extremely careful in this kind of position. If White's pieces coordinate, everything could go wrong ! I have already mentioned before, in this book, how I once made a draw against Movsesian in a winning position. It's time to show you how to win, because the same topic is connected to this game ! }
*

